<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authority="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous, 2022" authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Blennocampa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Blennocampa confusa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusa" status="sp. rev.">Blennocampa confusa</taxonomicName>
Konow, 1886b: 82. ♀. Type locality: Germany. Neotype ♀ (ZMHB) designated by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnd.4810350421" author="Koch, F" journalOrPublisher="Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="311 - 330" refId="B81" refString="Koch, F, 1988. Die Gattung Claremontia Rohwer (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae). Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 35 (4-5): 311 - 330, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnd.4810350421" title="Die Gattung Claremontia Rohwer (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnd.4810350421" volume="35" year="1988">Koch (1988)</bibRefCitation>
. Synonymy with 
<taxonomicName authority="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous, 2022" authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Claremontia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Claremontia brevicornis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis" status="sp. rev.">Claremontia brevicornis</taxonomicName>
proposed by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnd.4810350421" author="Koch, F" journalOrPublisher="Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="311 - 330" refId="B81" refString="Koch, F, 1988. Die Gattung Claremontia Rohwer (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae). Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 35 (4-5): 311 - 330, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnd.4810350421" title="Die Gattung Claremontia Rohwer (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnd.4810350421" volume="35" year="1988">Koch (1988)</bibRefCitation>
, wherein he overlooked the priority of the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous, 2022" authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Claremontia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Claremontia brevicornis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis" status="sp. rev.">Claremontia brevicornis</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Blank, SM" editor="Taeger, A" journalOrPublisher="Kommentierte Bestandsaufnahme. Goecke and Evers, Keltern" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="141 - 174" refId="B17" refString="Blank, SM, Taeger, A, 1998. Comments on the taxonomy of Symphyta (Hymenoptera) (Preliminary studies for a catalogue of Symphyta, part 4). In: Taeger, A, Blank, SM, Eds., Pflanzenwespen Deutschlands (Hymenoptera, Symphyta). Kommentierte Bestandsaufnahme. Goecke and Evers, Keltern: 141 - 174" title="Comments on the taxonomy of Symphyta (Hymenoptera) (Preliminary studies for a catalogue of Symphyta, part 4)." volumeTitle="Pflanzenwespen Deutschlands (Hymenoptera, Symphyta)." year="1998">Blank and Taeger 1998</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous, 2022" authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Monophadnoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Monophadnoides confusa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusa" status="sp. rev.">Monophadnoides confusa</taxonomicName>
: 
<bibRefCitation author="Benson, RB" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B10" refString="Benson, RB, 1952. Hymenoptera, Symphyta. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 6(2b): 51-137." title="Hymenoptera, Symphyta. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 6 (2 b): 51 - 137." year="1952">Benson (1952)</bibRefCitation>
; treated as species distinct from 
<taxonomicName authority="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous, 2022" authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. puncticeps" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="puncticeps" status="sp. rev.">M. puncticeps</taxonomicName>
, cultivated 
<taxonomicName authority="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous, 2022" authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Fragaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Fragaria" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" status="sp. rev.">Fragaria</taxonomicName>
species recorded as hosts of larva.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
Substantiating the statement about the host plant by 
<bibRefCitation author="Benson, RB" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B10" refString="Benson, RB, 1952. Hymenoptera, Symphyta. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 6(2b): 51-137." title="Hymenoptera, Symphyta. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 6 (2 b): 51 - 137." year="1952">Benson (1952)</bibRefCitation>
, the ZMUO specimens, collected in the Helsinki area, were reared from larvae feeding on cultivated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Fragaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Fragaria" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Fragaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
